<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-34-0975 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author first introduces a precise working definition of the term anticipatorypolicy. On this basis, certain characteristics of anticipatory policyare then described, including advantages and limitations. The role ofthree elements of anticipatory policy is analysed in more detail, i.e.of technical rationality, political viability, and demonstrable evidence.The author then identifies and elaborates upon various courses of actionwith which decision-makers may try to implement anticipatory strategiesof environmental policy. (orig./HSCH).</TEXT></DOC>